russel-french.name: Russel French
russel-french.title: Senior Mobile Developer
russel-french.about: Russel is a passionate mobile developer with 8+ years of experience building high-performance iOS and Android apps. He loves TypeScript, React Native, and mentoring junior devs.

customFields.question: What was your most challenging project?
customFields.description: A cross-platform fintech app with real-time sync and offline support.

answers.author: Russel
answers.text: Building a fintech app for both iOS and Android with real-time sync and offline support was a huge challenge. I led a team of 4 and we shipped on time!

ola-hopkins.name: Ola Hopkins
ola-hopkins.title: Backend Engineer
ola-hopkins.about: Ola is a backend specialist with a love for Go and distributed systems. He has built scalable APIs for startups and enjoys Docker and Kubernetes.

customFields.question: How do you ensure API reliability?
customFields.description: Automated tests, monitoring, and graceful error handling.

answers.author: Ola
answers.text: I use integration tests, Prometheus monitoring, and always return clear error messages for clients.

randall-swanson.name: Randall Swanson
randall-swanson.title: UI/UX Designer
randall-swanson.about: Randall is a creative UI/UX designer with a knack for branding and micro-interactions. He has worked with agencies and loves Figma and prototyping.

customFields.question: Favorite design tool?
customFields.description: Figma for collaboration, Principle for animation.

answers.author: Randall
answers.text: Figma is my go-to for UI, but I use Principle for prototyping animations.

olive-james.name: Olive James
olive-james.title: Fullstack Developer
olive-james.about: Olive is a fullstack developer who loves React and Django. She enjoys building GraphQL APIs and teaching coding to kids.

customFields.question: How do you keep learning?
customFields.description: Online courses, open source, and teaching others.

answers.author: Olive
answers.text: I take online courses, contribute to open source, and run a local kids code club.

elmer-robinson.name: Elmer Robinson
elmer-robinson.title: DevOps Engineer
elmer-robinson.about: Elmer is a DevOps engineer who automates everything. He loves AWS, Terraform, and building CI/CD pipelines for fast, safe deployments.

answers.author: Elmer
answers.text: Terraform lets me manage cloud infra as code and keep everything versioned.

henry-edwards.name: Henry Edwards
henry-edwards.title: Frontend Engineer
henry-edwards.about: Henry is a frontend engineer who loves Vue.js and beautiful UIs. He is a Storybook advocate and enjoys writing tests with Jest.

answers.author: Henry
answers.text: Sass makes my CSS so much more maintainable and readable.

kate-brock.name: Kate Brock
kate-brock.title: Product Manager
kate-brock.about: Kate is a product manager who loves agile teams and user research. She has launched 10+ products and is a certified Scrum Master.

customFields.question: How do you prioritize features?
customFields.description: User feedback, business value, and dev effort.

answers.author: Kate
answers.text: I use a weighted scoring model and always talk to users before finalizing the roadmap.

nancy-duncan.name: Nancy Duncan
nancy-duncan.title: QA Engineer
nancy-duncan.about: Nancy is a QA engineer who automates everything. She loves Cypress, API testing, and finding edge cases others miss.

customFields.question: How do you write good test cases?
customFields.description: Think like a user, cover edge cases, automate when possible.

answers.author: Nancy
answers.text: I always start with user stories, then write tests for every edge case I can imagine.

rosetta-alvarez.name: Rosetta Alvarez
rosetta-alvarez.title: Data Scientist
rosetta-alvarez.about: Rosetta is a data scientist who loves machine learning and R. She has published papers on NLP and enjoys Kaggle competitions.

customFields.question: Favorite ML project?
customFields.description: A chatbot for Spanish banking customers.

answers.author: Rosetta
answers.text: I built a Spanish-language chatbot for a bank using TensorFlow and spaCy.

zachary-murray.name: Zachary Murray
zachary-murray.title: Cloud Architect
zachary-murray.about: Zachary is a cloud architect with a focus on Azure and GCP. He designs secure, scalable cloud systems for global companies.

customFields.question: Most complex cloud migration?
customFields.description: Moving a legacy ERP to GCP with zero downtime.

answers.author: Zachary
answers.text: Migrated a 20-year-old ERP system to GCP with zero downtime and full data integrity.
